The paper deals with coded caching, which is a technique used in information theory (cs.IT) to reduce rate in cached networks. The focus of the paper is on privacy for user demands, which is a topic in network security (cs.NI). The paper also discusses subpacketization, which is a concept in distributed systems (cs.DS) and coding theory (cs.IT). The paper presents a new linear demand-private scheme, which involves coding and decoding algorithms, making it relevant to coding theory (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the reduction of subpacketization when there are a large number of files, which is a topic in systems and networking (cs.SI).
